    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-12-13T15:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-12-13T15:45:00-05:00" n="630"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d630">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–1352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d630fn1">Drafted by <persName>Jones</persName>, <gloss
                            target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>; cleared with the geographic bureaus
                        (except <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>); and signed by the Deputy
                        Director of the Office of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Political and
                        Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_POPPERDH1"
                        >Popper</persName>).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-12-13T15:45:00-05:00"
                            >December 13, 1952—3:45 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 99. Re Membership (<gloss
                        target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss>s 358 and 359): <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> agrees your present plan submit
                            separate res on Japan if this is what Japan wants.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> cld not support draft res of Peru
                            or draft res of Costa Rica, El Salvador, Honduras and Nicaragua, and we
                            hope both will be referred to Special Comite and not put to vote.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Re suggested composition of Special Comite contained in draft res of
                            all central American states, <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                            believes Thailand or Philippines shld be represented and suggests one of
                            them be substituted for Egypt, or if this is not feasible, be added as
                            additional member. Hope <gloss target="#t_GADel1">GADel</gloss> can
                            encourage this change.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
